---
import PortalLayout from "../layouts/PortalLayout.astro";
---

<PortalLayout title="Playbook">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Playbook</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8">Architecture, workflows, and standards for every site we build</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════
           1. FULL STACK
      ════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Full Stack</h2>
        <ol class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span>
            <div><strong>Claude (<a href="https://claude.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">claude.ai</a>)</strong> — conversational updates and builds</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span>
            <div><strong>Astro + Tailwind CSS</strong> — pages and styling</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span>
            <div><strong>GitHub (<a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Spirit-Media-US</a>)</strong> — code only, never media</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span>
            <div><strong>Netlify</strong> — hosting, auto-deploys on push to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">main</code></div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — domain, SSL, CDN, security</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">6.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — all images, audio, video</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">7.</span>
            <div><strong>Sanity (<a href="https://sanity.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">sanity.io</a>)</strong> — CMS for client content editing and media management with auto-optimization (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">8.</span>
            <div><strong>GoHighLevel</strong> — CRM &amp; forms for internal sites, tagged by ministry (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">9.</span>
            <div><strong>Google Docs MCP</strong> — documents, proposals, reports, content drafts</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">10.</span>
            <div><strong>Stitch</strong> (Google Stitch 2.0) — AI-powered design, generates pages and design systems (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">11.</span>
            <div><strong>Playwright</strong> — browser testing, screenshots, cross-browser QA (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">12.</span>
            <div><strong>UptimeRobot</strong> — uptime monitoring (every 5 min, all sites)</div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════
           2. TOOL REFERENCE (single consolidated section)
      ════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <section class="bg-violet-50 border border-violet-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-violet-700 mb-2">Tool Reference</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-2">Run all tools from your own Claude session. SSH into Bethel as yourself, then:</p>
        <code class="block bg-white border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mb-6">cd ~/Sites/&lt;slug&gt; && claude</code>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Start Migration</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Creates GitHub repo, Sanity project, Netlify site, and scaffold. Run from <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">~/Sites</code> (not inside a site dir).</p>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Start migration for [Site Name] — slug: [slug], client URL: https://...</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Continue Migration</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Resumes from the current phase. Claude checks progress and picks up where you left off.</p>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">continue migration</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Start New Site Build</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Creates GitHub repo, Sanity project, Netlify site, and scaffold. Run from <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">~/Sites</code>.</p>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Start new site build for [Site Name] — slug: [slug]</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Continue Newsite</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Resumes from the current phase. Claude checks progress and picks up where you left off.</p>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">continue newsite</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
              <div>
                <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Pre-Launch QA</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">8 code scans + build gate. Generates a Google Doc report. Use at Phase 5 (The Gate) and Phase 7 (QA).</p>
              </div>
              <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1LiDlC_0SddKGXBpgAqlydUVWeLGdLZ2R?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-xs font-semibold text-violet-700 hover:underline shrink-0 ml-4">Drive &rarr;</a>
            </div>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Run Pre-Launch QA</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
              <div>
                <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Post-Launch QA</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Lighthouse + SEO + accessibility on the live URL. Auto-fixes what it can, generates a Google Doc report.</p>
              </div>
              <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1igaRd2Ed_Bat--5EnX0TlaSyCLjmcSnL?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-xs font-semibold text-violet-700 hover:underline shrink-0 ml-4">Drive &rarr;</a>
            </div>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Run Post-Launch QA on https://[domain]</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
              <div>
                <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Site Audit &amp; Optimization Report</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Client-ready Google Doc — performance, SEO, accessibility, recommendations. Run after Post-Launch QA passes.</p>
              </div>
              <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1ekM2jpMHWFLou0cF7vbZYH2sIKL8kaoV?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-xs font-semibold text-violet-700 hover:underline shrink-0 ml-4">Drive &rarr;</a>
            </div>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Run Site Audit Report on https://[domain]</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Blog Protocol</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Adds a full blog — search, categories, pagination, related posts, share bar, SEO. Kevin customizes later.</p>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Use our blog protocol and add a blog to this site</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Request a Site Update</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Make content or code changes. Describe what you want — Claude edits and pushes to dev.</p>
            <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">[Describe the change you want]</code>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-400 mt-1">Example: "Change the hero headline to 'Walking in Freedom' and update the button to say 'Start Your Journey'"</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════
           3. WEBSITE MIGRATION PROTOCOL
      ════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <section class="bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-rose-700 mb-1">Website Migration Protocol</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-1">Client-facing name: <strong>The Transformation System</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pipeline type: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">migration</code></p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-5">Clone an existing client website to the SMP stack. 9 phases — Claude does the work, you verify at checkpoints.</p>

        <!-- How to run -->
        <div class="bg-white border border-rose-200 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-rose-800 text-sm mb-3">How to run a migration</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal ml-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
            <li><strong>SSH into Bethel as yourself</strong> (not deploy) and start Claude:<br/>
              <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono mt-1 inline-block">cd ~/Sites && claude</code></li>
            <li>Say: <code class="bg-rose-100 border border-rose-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono">"Start migration for [Site Name] — slug: [slug], client URL: https://..."</code></li>
            <li>When Phase 1 completes, move into the site directory:<br/>
              <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono mt-1 inline-block">cd ~/Sites/&lt;slug&gt; && claude</code></li>
            <li>Say <strong>"continue migration"</strong> — Claude reads the protocol, checks which phase you're on, and starts working.</li>
            <li>Claude pauses at checkpoints. It pushes to dev and gives you the Netlify preview URL.</li>
            <li>Say <strong>"continue"</strong> — Claude advances to the next phase. If a session ends, say "continue migration" again.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Media rules -->
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-amber-800 text-sm mb-2">Media rules — no exceptions</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-sm">
            <div><strong class="text-stone-700">Images</strong><br/><span class="text-stone-500">Sanity CMS. Auto-optimized CDN. Never in Git.</span></div>
            <div><strong class="text-stone-700">Audio</strong><br/><span class="text-stone-500">Cloudflare R2. Manual upload.</span></div>
            <div><strong class="text-stone-700">Video</strong><br/><span class="text-stone-500">YouTube iframe embed. Never &lt;video&gt; tag.</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- The 9 Phases -->
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">1</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Infrastructure</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-rose-700 bg-rose-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">AUTOMATED</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Creates GitHub repo, Netlify site, Sanity project. Clones to Bethel. Sets up Astro 5 + Tailwind v4 scaffold, CLAUDE.md, .gitignore, dev branch. Adds the site card to the <a href="/dashboard" class="text-rose-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Dashboard</a>.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Verify GitHub, Netlify, and Sanity links exist. The site card appears on the Dashboard with <strong>Dev</strong> and <strong>Main</strong> preview buttons — use these throughout the build to preview your work on Netlify without running a local dev server.</p>
              <p><strong>Advances automatically</strong> when infrastructure is created.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Content + CSS Extraction</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Uses Playwright to crawl the original site at desktop (1280px) and mobile (375px). Extracts all content, computed CSS (colors, fonts, sizes, spacing), navigation structure, and catalogs all images.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Verify <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">content/design-tokens.md</code> has real values. Page count in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">pages/</code> matches <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">site-inventory.md</code>.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when verified.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Design + Build</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-rose-600 bg-rose-50 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Stitch MCP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Creates a Stitch project and design system from extracted CSS tokens. Generates screens for every page. Writes <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">global.css</code> from design tokens BEFORE building pages. Builds all Astro pages using CSS variables only.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Compare Netlify preview against the original site. Colors, fonts, spacing, navigation, mobile.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when the site matches the original.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Wire Sanity CMS</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Uploads images to Sanity. Defines schemas. Migrates content. Wires Astro pages to fetch from Sanity. Deploys schema. Sets up Sanity → Netlify webhook. If the site needs a blog, say <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">Use our blog protocol</code>.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Images loading from Sanity CDN? Schemas and docs look right in Studio? Edit a doc — does the change appear?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when CMS is wired and working.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="border-2 border-rose-400 bg-white rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">5</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-rose-800">CAR / Transformation Layer Report</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-white bg-rose-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">THE GATE</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-rose-700 text-sm font-semibold mb-3 ml-10">Nothing past Phase 5 until all critical fixes are resolved.</p>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Runs Migration Fidelity checklist. Generates Transformation Layer Report (Google Doc) with Part One (delivered), Part Two (critical fixes), Part Three (improvements). Implements all critical fixes. Say <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">Run Pre-Launch QA</code> to generate the 8-scan report.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Review the report. Preview the site — are critical fixes resolved?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when all criticals are fixed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">6</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Design Refinement</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-rose-600 bg-rose-50 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Stitch MCP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Takes improvements from CAR Part Three. Uses Stitch to generate design variants. Implements refinements in Astro. Site goes from "faithful clone" to "better than the original."</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Preview the site. Does it look better? Desktop + mobile.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when satisfied.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">7</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">QA</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-rose-700 bg-rose-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">AUTOMATED + MANUAL</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Lighthouse audit, cross-browser testing (Playwright), form testing, console errors, mobile responsiveness. Fixes everything found. Say <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">Run Pre-Launch QA</code> — all 8 scans must pass.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Lighthouse scores. Pre-Launch QA report is clean.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when all checks pass.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">8</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Launch</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Merges dev to main (<strong>requires Kevin's approval</strong>). Connects custom domain, Cloudflare DNS, SSL. Verifies all pages load, forms work, GA4 fires, sitemap in Search Console, UptimeRobot active, Open Graph correct. Say <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">Run Post-Launch QA on https://[domain]</code> then <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">Run Site Audit Report on https://[domain]</code>.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Visit the live site. GA4 real-time. Share URL on social — preview card looks right?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when everything is live.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">9</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Client Delivery &amp; Roadmap</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Generates client delivery email and post-launch roadmap (Google Doc). Invites client to Sanity Studio.</p>
              <p><strong>You do:</strong> Send the delivery email to the client.</p>
              <div class="mt-3">
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-1">Delivery email template:</p>
                <div class="relative">
                  <div class="bg-stone-100 px-3 py-2 rounded text-sm text-stone-600 whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed" id="delivery-email">Subject: Your website is live! — [Site Name]

Hi [Client Name],

Your new website is live at [domain]!

We've put together a guide to help you manage your site content on your own:
&rarr; https://portal.spiritmediapublishing.com/clients

To set up your team's content editing access, please reply with the name and email address for each person who should be able to edit. We'll send them a Sanity Studio invite with everything they need to get started.

For anything beyond content edits — new pages, design changes, forms, or technical work — just email us at hello@spiritmediapublishing.com.

Welcome aboard!
SMP Team</div>
                  <button class="copy-btn absolute top-2 right-2 px-3 py-1 bg-rose-50 hover:bg-rose-100 text-rose-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold font-sans" data-copy-target="delivery-email">Copy</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════
           4. NEW SITE BUILD PROTOCOL
      ════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
      <section class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-1">SMP Build Protocol (New Sites)</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-1">Client-facing name: <strong>The Build System</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pipeline type: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">newsite</code></p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-5">Build a brand new website from scratch. 9 phases — Claude does the work, you verify at checkpoints.</p>

        <!-- How to run -->
        <div class="bg-white border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-blue-800 text-sm mb-3">How to run a new site build</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal ml-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
            <li><strong>SSH into Bethel as yourself</strong> (not deploy) and start Claude:<br/>
              <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono mt-1 inline-block">cd ~/Sites && claude</code></li>
            <li>Say: <code class="bg-blue-100 border border-blue-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono">"Start new site build for [Site Name] — slug: [slug]"</code></li>
            <li>When infrastructure is ready, move into the site directory:<br/>
              <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono mt-1 inline-block">cd ~/Sites/&lt;slug&gt; && claude</code></li>
            <li>Say <strong>"continue newsite"</strong> — Claude starts Phase 1 (Discovery &amp; Brand).</li>
            <li>Claude pauses at checkpoints. It gives you the preview URL.</li>
            <li>Say <strong>"continue"</strong> — Claude advances to the next phase.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- The 9 Phases -->
        <div class="space-y-6">
